                    </h2>
                </div>
                <div class=col-md-12><button class=accordion>What is a Web design agency?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>A web design agency will probably have a professional web/graphic designer working on website UI such as themes, logos, color patterns, and any other brand object. Many software such as Adobe Photo Shop, Illustrator, after-effects are the key ingredient to producing quality web design for businesses, welfare or an ecommerce store.</p>
                    </div><button class=accordion>How do you design a website? (Web design process)</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>Following is simple process we used to follow, however it can be changed as per the client requirements. </p>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Define your objective regarding the website.</li>
                          <li>Plot the theme for your site. Using right colors, font type, etc. which reflects your product or service.</li>
                          <li>Use creative and instinctive design samples as per your requirements.</li>
                          <li>Sample submission and approval</li>
                          <li>Placing additional items including side navigation, CTRs, etc.</li>
                          <li>Making modifications as per feedback.</li>
                          <li>Making it available publically.</li>
                          <li>Enjoy your professional website :D</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><button class=accordion>How many hours does it take to make a website?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>It completely depends upon the nature of the website and requirements. If design and implementation are straightforward then probably 75 to 100 hours (8 to 10 business days) are enough for static 5 pages. The front end of the website would take almost 30–40 hours to complete. If it's more complex, then 50–75 hours each for design and development would be enough.</p>
                    </div><button class=accordion>What are the design elements of a website?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>The 7 types of logos (and how to use them)</p>
                  <ul>
                     <li>Overall Layout of the website and Visual appearance. </li>
                     <li>Color Scheme – Theme and combinations</li>
                     <li>Typography - Text and fonts</li>
                     <li>Navigation on the website – User friendly</li>
                     <li>Content – Copyright free</li>
                     <li>Mobile UI friendly</li>
                     

                  </ul>
                    </div>
                    <button class=accordion>How do I choose a web design company or web designer?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>You can find best web Design Company on Google, the results can be according to your current location or city (or within your industry). Review websites portfolio, qualified staff, and quality of service they provide.  Website Valley is one of the leading web design agency in San Francisco, California and other regions of US and around the globe. You can directly talk with our support team regarding your requirements. </p>
                    </div>
                    <button class=accordion>What is the main difference between web development & design?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>Fundamentally, web design relates to both the graphics part and usability. On the other hand development take actual functioning of the website. It use coding, CSS, Dot-net, PHP, HTML, Javascript, and more programming languages.</p>
                    </div>
    
                    <button class=accordion>Can I buy a name of my website?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>Yes we will buy a name of your website. You just need to share the name you want to purchase and will do it for you. The name of the website is called “Domain Name”.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button class=accordion>Do I need to pay extra for website name and hosting?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>It depends on the selected package, if it is included then No.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button class=accordion>What do you look for in a good web design company?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>The web design company you select must be capable to understand your company's mission and vision. Also, check if they offers complete brand identity rather just limited to specific region, and turn it into an appealing website that connects with potential customers.  
                        <br>
                        The company should be able to help you reach your potential audience and meet your business objectives. A web design agency must have both the artistic web designers, with out of the box ideas and good technical and creative skills, and a marketing team that must have information of how to drive traffic to your website, encourage visitor engagement, and transform visitors into customers. The best web design agency understand current web design trends, must have experience building websites in a variety of niche or industries, and has an extensive portfolio of live websites.
               
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <button class=accordion>How much website design cost?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                        <p>Websites cost depends upon nature, size, features, and technicalities required to build of a website. Expect to pay $300 to create a website with a default website builder however you need to have good technical background and need to invest months to get the final product. On an average $500 to $5000 to build a site with a freelancer. Lastly but most importantly and conveniently you can hire a professional web design agency to do the complete task for you and they are charging somewhere less than freelancer but the quality is outstanding.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>What should you look for when hiring a web design agency?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Previous client work and examples – Check Online review for the web design agency.</li>
                        <li>Advancement &amp; Technicalities - Must be up to date with latest web design trend and should have a team of experts in every domain</li>
                        <li>Cost – should not be charging very less and also make sure you are not purchasing the services of the most expensive ones. Keep it moderate and don’t compromise on the quality of the work.</li>
                        <li>Experience with your web type – Must have expertise regarding the development platform and industry in which you are looking to get the task done.</li>
                        
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>What is digital web design & functionalities or customer web journey?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>Web design functionalities is what makes the overall feel, look and process of customer when you're using a website. This process includes the planning and building the elements of your website in such a way that the visitor can easily navigate and reach to the desire page without spending much time or let say within 3 clicks. It includes elements from basic structure &amp; layout to colors, fonts, design and graphics to chat, form submissions, breadcrumbs, page length, content placement, link structure, etc. When you're building a website, you require both web design development kit and good functional journey.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>Is Web design and graphic design are the same?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>No, they have some differences Web Design is the creation of graphics, typography, graphs, and images to communicate an idea. It only refer to websites, not print. Web Designers are responsible for creating websites that not only look good but load quickly as well making a responsive web design – Responsive UI for both desktop and mobile. On the other hand graphic design is creation of overall brand from print to online material. It includes stationery, banners, brochures, social media pages, etc. Web design is a part of graphics.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>What services we provide to clients?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>At  Website Valley, we provide you the best online branding solutions along with several other digital services. We’re 360-degree online branding and digital marketing agency that provides all solutions to its clients all over the world in 14 different countries.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>Are there any limitations on geographical bases for clients?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>No, there isn’t. Our experts work with clients and customers all over the world. We’ve worked with clients from all industries and have successfully transformed them into giant corporations in general. Our team’s mission is for a perfectly digital planet and for that we like to work with international corporations all the time.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>Can I do web design on my own?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>Yes, however it is possible to learn first and then you can.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>Can I host my own website? </button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>No, you need any hosting service provider to host your own website. Also you need some technical information to host the domain and making it live. You need to throw a few HTML files into a hosting folder and make them live on the internet. We don't suggest you to do this technical stuff yourself or simple don’t try to host your own website as it will definitely bring some performance and technical issues.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>What are the main design elements of a website?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>There are many elements need to be considered but following are 6 main design elements you'll have to make sure you get them right.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Overall look and feel with visual appearance of the theme. Site overall look is really important and of course it is a vital factor of this process. </li>
                        <li>Color Scheme including combinations, fonts, etc.</li>
                        <li>Navigation and functionality of the pages and features.</li>
                        <li>Content and number of pages. </li>
                        <li>Always remember the Mobile and tablet performance.</li>
                    </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>How to analyze a website design?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>Following are the main 6 ways to weigh the Quality of any website design:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Strategy. Create a strong strategy and then start. </li>
                        <li>Usability. It is second in the row and it is all about the practical considerations of what makes into design. The user-friendliness, protocols, speed, coding, other details like robtos,txt, sitemaps, etc. ... </li>
                        <li>Style. Font size, images, etc.</li>
                        <li>Content. Number of pages, word count, etc.</li>
                        <li>Search Engine Optimization. Keywords frequency, density, AMP, etc.</li>
                        <li>Social. Place social media accounts, live tweets, etc.</li>
                    </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>Are there any hidden cost or additional fees included after order completion?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>Not at all. We will provide you all features as mentioned in selected deal or package without paying a single penny. Also if required you certainly can purchase any additional services at any time.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <button class=accordion>What is required to place an order?</button>
                    <div class=panel>
                    <p>Simply visit our contact us page or start chat with our representative, provide us your requirements, and it's done! Let our expert team provide you with an outstanding services.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
